ivardefs.name: code
ivardefs.desc: Describes what was observed. Sometimes this is called the observation "code".

ivardefs.name: dataAbsentReason
ivardefs.desc: Provides a reason why the expected value in the element Observation.component.value[x] is missing.

ivardefs.name: interpretation_
ivardefs.desc: A categorical assessment of an observation value.  For example, high, low, normal.

properties.desc: Some observations have multiple component observations.  These component observations are expressed as separate code value pairs that share the same attributes.  Examples include systolic and diastolic component observations for blood pressure measurement
